name: std::io::error::repr_bitpacked::kind_from_prim
src:
fn kind_from_prim(ek: u32) -> Option<ErrorKind> {
    macro_rules! from_prim {
        ($prim:expr => $Enum:ident { $($Variant:ident),* $(,)? }) => {{
            // Force a compile error if the list gets out of date.
            const _: fn(e: $Enum) = |e: $Enum| match e {
                $($Enum::$Variant => ()),*
            };
            match $prim {
                $(v if v == ($Enum::$Variant as _) => Some($Enum::$Variant),)*
                _ => None,
            }
        }}
    }
    from_prim!(ek => ErrorKind {
        NotFound,
        PermissionDenied,
        ConnectionRefused,
        ConnectionReset,
        HostUnreachable,
        NetworkUnreachable,
        ConnectionAborted,
        NotConnected,
        AddrInUse,
        AddrNotAvailable,
        NetworkDown,
        BrokenPipe,
        AlreadyExists,
        WouldBlock,
        NotADirectory,
        IsADirectory,
        DirectoryNotEmpty,
        ReadOnlyFilesystem,
        FilesystemLoop,
        StaleNetworkFileHandle,
        InvalidInput,
        InvalidData,
        TimedOut,
        WriteZero,
        StorageFull,
        NotSeekable,
        QuotaExceeded,
        FileTooLarge,
        ResourceBusy,
        ExecutableFileBusy,
        Deadlock,
        CrossesDevices,
        TooManyLinks,
        InvalidFilename,
        ArgumentListTooLong,
        Interrupted,
        Other,
        UnexpectedEof,
        Unsupported,
        OutOfMemory,
        InProgress,
        Uncategorized,
    })
}
